<p>Your telegram 406 of 4th June. [1] I entirely agree that a private undertaking communicated without publicity to Japanese Government is adequate. I expressed that view in London. I will ask Bruce [2] to advise the Foreign Office in that sense.</p>

<p>MENZIES</p>

<p>_</p>

<p>1 Document 485.</p>

<p>2 High Commissioner in London. Menzies sent Bruce an unnumbered cablegram On 7 June, repeating the text of Caseyâ€™s cablegram 406 and asking Bruce to pass it to the U.K. Foreign Office. See file AA: A981, Far East 26A.</p>

